The paper focuses on examining how people carry out search tasks online, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also looks at the impact of gender and age on search behavior, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) and cyberpsychology (cs.CY). Additionally, the study involves analyzing data and performance, which could relate to social and information networks (cs.SI).
